# One Responsibility, One Name

Give each function and class **one clear job**. Its name should state that job.

The reader should understand *what this unit does* from its name alone. If you
cannot name it without "and" or "or," split it. A function that "checks whether
we should check a function" is `_should_check_function`. A function that "runs
checks on a module" is `run_checks`. The name is a promise; the body fulfills it.

Classes the same: `Parent` contains children; `Function` is a function with
signature and docstring; `Failure` compiles and produces the report. No mixed
purposes. When a class grows many concerns, extract or split so each type has
one life, one reason to exist.
